Section: x11
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Andrew Crew Kuznetsov <andrewcrew@rambler.ru>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5), cdbs, autotools-dev, pkg-config, kdelibs5-dev, libxneur-dev (>= 0.15.0), libtool, docbook-to-man, libqt4-dev (>= 4.6)
Standards-Version: 3.8.4
Homepage: http://xneur.ru

Package: kdeneur
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, xneur (>= 0.16.0)
Section: kde
Priority: extra
Description: KDE frontend for xneur keyboard layout switcher. 
 kdeneur runs in system tray and shows XNeur's state. It also allows to configure
 XNeur via GUI dialog.
 .
 XNeur is an in-place converter of text typed in with a wrong keyboard layout.
 See xneur package for more info.
